http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Police-officer-wins-award/article14015295.ece

C.V. Vidyadharan, a police officer, has been selected for the annual award instituted by the Dr. Sukumar Azhikode Vichara Vedi, Alappuzha, for environmental protection. The award, consisting of Rs.10,001, citation and statuette, will be given away at a function to be held at Thottappally on January 24.Announcing the name of the recipient, Vedi representatives said Mr. Vidyadharan had been making efforts to plant saplings in large numbers. He had planted about 40,000 plants so far and had taken care to nurture them at public places and compounds of institutions.